Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place chicken on one side of #oven-ready tray{} (for 4 servings, place all the chicken in one tray). Top chicken with @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}.

Open package of @seasoned precooked potato slices{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Place potatoes in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, separating any pieces that are stuck together. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; poke a few holes in wrap and microwave for ~{3%minutes}. Toss with a drizzle of @cooking oil{} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Transfer seasoned potatoes to opposite side of tray from chicken (for 4 servings, transfer potatoes to a second tray). Top potatoes with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake on middle rack (be sure your oven has preheated!) until chicken is cooked through and potatoes are browned, ~{25-30%minutes}. (For 4, bake two trays side by side on middle rack.)

Meanwhile, wash and dry #bowl{} used for potatoes.

In same bowl, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, salt, and pepper (all the vinegar and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Refrigerate until ready to serve.

Divide BBQ chicken, cheddar potatoes, and coleslaw between plates in separate sections. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.